      <abstract>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHAT?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para os="sles" arch="x86-64">
                This article describes how to install &sles; using &agama; on &x86-64; machines.
                The information presented here applies to installation of the products on both bare
                metal and virtual machines.
              </para>
              <para os="sles4sap" arch="x86-64">
                This article describes how to install &sles4sap; using &agama; on &x86-64;
                machines. The information presented here applies to installation of the products on
                both bare metal and virtual machines.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHY?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para os="sles" arch="x86-64">
                Read this article to understand the process of installing &sles; using &agama; on
                &x86-64; machines.
              </para>
              <para os="sles4sap" arch="x86-64">
                Read this article to understand the process of installing &sles4sap; using &agama;
                on &x86-64; machines.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>EFFORT</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                You may need 15 minutes to read this article.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>GOAL</term>
            <listitem>
              <para os="sles" arch="x86-64">
                Understand how to install &sles; using &agama; on &x86-64; machines.
              </para>
              <para os="sles4sap" arch="x86-64">
                Understand how to install &sles4sap; using &agama; on &x86-64; machines.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>REQUIREMENTS</term>
            <listitem>
              <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    An &x86-64; system &ndash; either bare metal or a virtual machine. For server
                    installations without any desktop environment, &suse; recommends a minimum of
                    1&nbsp;CPU, 2&nbsp;GB memory and 32&nbsp;GB storage (which includes storage for
                    Btrfs snapshots in the root partition, swap space, and storage for software
                    packages).
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    An active registration code for the product you want to install. You can
                    generate a registration code for the product and activate its subscription for
                    your organization at the &scc;.
                  </para>
                  <note>
                    <title>Optional registration</title>
                    <para>
                      Certain images that are signed with the developer's key may allow you to skip
                      registration before or while installation. Besides, certain images may
                      contain all installable packages for your operating system that you can use
                      as an offline package repository. In such cases, you may not need an active
                      registration code before installation. However, if you use software packages
                      from the official online repositories, &suse; recommends registering your
                      product with the &scc;.
                    </para>
                  </note>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
